Betsey Stockton (c. 1798–1865), sometimes spelled Betsy Stockton, was an African-American educator and missionary.

Life [ edit ]

Betsey was born into slavery in Princeton, New Jersey, about the year 1798. While she was a child, her owner Robert Stockton gave her to his daughter upon her marriage to Reverend Ashbel Green, president of the College of New Jersey (now Princeton University).
